                <span class="income-value">$21,675</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="income-note">That's from a single room. Hosts with 2-3 spare rooms can double or triple this figure. And remember: entire-unit hosts are capped at 180 nights regardless of demand.</p>
          </div>

          <h3>The Comparison That Matters</h3>
          <p>With entire-unit registration at $200/night for 180 nights, you'd earn $36,000. Sounds better than $21,675, right?</p>
          <p>But here's the thing: that entire-unit host can't earn anything from STR for the remaining 185 nights. Meanwhile, the partial-unit host keeps earning, and can also rent during high-demand periods like TIFF, Pride, and Caribana when rates spike.</p>

